<i>adverb</i>: 화평히 [화평히], 평안히 [평안히], 원만히 [원만히], 씨근씨근 [씨근씨근], 쌔근쌔근 [쌔근쌔근], 소록소록 [소록쏘록], 둥글둥글 [둥글둥글], 고요히 [고요히] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>화평히 [화평히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. peacefully; harmoniously</dd><br>
<dd>마음속이나 사람들 사이에 갈등이 없이 평화롭게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being mentally peaceful or living at peace with others without any conflict.</dd><br>
<dd>2. peacefully; harmoniously</dd><br>
<dd>나라 사이에 충돌이나 전쟁이 없이 평화롭게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of two or more countries being at peace with each other without any conflict or war.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>평안히 [평안히]</dt><br>
<dd>peacefully; well</dd><br>
<dd>걱정이나 탈이 없이. 또는 무사히 잘 있는 상태로.</dd><br>
<dd>Without any worries or troubles, or in a healthy and safe state.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>원만히 [원만히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. mildly; gently</dd><br>
<dd>성격이 부드럽고 너그럽게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of one's personality being gentle and generous.</dd><br>
<dd>2. smoothly; peacefully</dd><br>
<dd>일의 진행이 순조롭게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state in which the progress of something is smooth.</dd><br>
<dd>3. intimately; harmoniously</dd><br>
<dd>서로 사이가 좋게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of getting along well with each other.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>씨근씨근 [씨근씨근]</dt><br>
<dd>1. pantingly; out of breath</dd><br>
<dd>고르지 않고 거칠고 가쁘게 자꾸 숨 쉬는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating or describing the sound or manner of breathing irregularly, roughly, and hard.</dd><br>
<dd>2. calmly; peacefully</dd><br>
<dd>어린아이가 깊이 잠들어 매우 조용하게 자꾸 숨 쉬는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating or describing the sound or manner of a child breathing very quietly while sleeping.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>쌔근쌔근 [쌔근쌔근]</dt><br>
<dd>1. pantingly; out of breath</dd><br>
<dd>조금 거칠게 자꾸 숨 쉬는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating or describing the sound or manner of breathing a little roughly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. calmly; peacefully</dd><br>
<dd>어린아이가 깊이 잠들어 조용하게 자꾸 숨 쉬는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating or describing the sound or manner of a child breathing quietly while being fast asleep.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>소록소록 [소록쏘록]</dt><br>
<dd>1. quietly; peacefully</dd><br>
<dd>아기가 포근하고 곱게 자는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state of a baby sleeping comfortably and adorably.</dd><br>
<dd>2. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>비나 눈 등이 조용히 내리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state of rain or snow falling quietly.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>둥글둥글 [둥글둥글]</dt><br>
<dd>1. round</dd><br>
<dd>여럿이 모두 또는 매우 둥근 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state in which all of several things are very round.</dd><br>
<dd>2. amicably; peacefully; harmoniously</dd><br>
<dd>성격이 까다롭지 않고 매우 부드럽고 너그러운 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>With a personality of being very soft, generous, and not fussy.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>고요히 [고요히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. silently</dd><br>
<dd>시끄럽거나 어지럽지 않고 조용하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Quietly, neither noisily nor confusedly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. serenely; calmly</dd><br>
<dd>강이나 바다 등의 물결이 잔잔하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a river, the sea, etc., flowing with small ripples.</dd><br>
<dd>3. peacefully; serenely</dd><br>
<dd>마음이나 상태 등이 조용하고 평화롭게.</dd><br>
<dd>With a quiet and peaceful mind or in such a state.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>